[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T16:32:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/textentry3-0eebc.gif?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Narrative adventure titles are getting the spotlight they deserve at GOG, where you can save on both new and old entries in the genre. We love this year\u2019s <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/impressions/446232/crimson-diamond-julia-minamata-text-parser-review-impressions-interview\">The Crimson Diamond</a></em> for its modern retreading of classic titles (even if its text parser interface is occasionally awkward). If you\u2019d like to try your hand at cracking the case, you can currently pick it up from GOG for just <a href=\"https://www.gog.com/en/game/the_crimson_diamond\">$13.49</a> (was $14.99). </p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Other highlights include the <a hre", "id": 1337741, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/sales-guide/466289/point-click-myst-narrative-adventure-games-deal-gog", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Crimson Diamond and other narrative gems are cheaper for a limited time at GOG", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T16:30:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Blizzard Entertainment via Polygon\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/chorus/uploads/chorus_asset/file/24711856/Diablo_4_Screenshot_2023.06.08___12.57.14.95.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>Like all great RPGs, reaching the <strong>level cap</strong> and <strong>Item Power</strong> max in <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/diablo-4/40629\"><em>Diablo 4</em></a> is the pinnacle endgame goal everyone chases. How can you make your character as strong as they can possibly be? You hit the max level, of course!</p>\n\n<p>While the idea of max level used to be very complex in <em>Diablo 4</em>, Blizzard has simplified it significantly with the <em>Vessel of Hatred</em> expansion. The idea of loot breakpoints are also mostly gone, and getting loot is less about the numerical \u201cItem Powe", "id": 1337742, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/diablo-4-guides/23753834/level-cap-item-power-breakpoint", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "What is the level cap and max Item Power in Diablo 4?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T16:17:15+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"GTA Online promo art for Ghosts Exposed\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Rockstar Games\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/GTA-Online-10102024-5.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>Ghosts have appeared around Los Santos in <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gta-online-guides\"><em><strong>GTA Online</strong></em></a> with this week\u2019s Halloween-themed update. The in-universe show, <strong>Ghosts Exposed</strong>, is back and paying for photos of the apparitions.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Our <em>GTA Online </em>Ghosts Exposed guide will tell where \u2014 and, just as importantly, <em>when</em> \u2014 you can find all 10 ghosts.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-css-opacity\" />\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"tqxGpX\"><strong>How to start the Ghosts Exposed challenge in GTA Online</strong></h2>\n\n<p class=", "id": 1337743, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gta-online-guides/466073/ghost-locations-where-to-find-exposed", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Where to find all ghosts in GTA Online", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T16:14:38+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"An anime woman in an orange space suit floating with the Earth visible in the background in Planetes.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: Sunrise/Crunchyroll\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/image-w1280.jpeg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">For anime fans of a certain age, <em>Planetes</em> is one of the holy grails of sci-fi animation. Produced in 2003 by Sunrise (<em>Cowboy Bebop</em>, <em>Mobile Suit Gundam</em>), directed by Gor\u014d Taniguchi (<em>Code Geass: Lelouch of the Rebellion</em>), and based on the manga of the same name by Makoto Yukimura (<em>Vinland Saga</em>), the 26-episode series about working-class space-debris salvagers has been elusive for North American fans looking for a legal way to watch it \u2014 until now.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">On Tuesday, Crunchy", "id": 1337744, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/anime/466462/planetes-anime-crunchyroll-streaming-bluray-release-date", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Sci-fi anime cult classic Planetes is finally streaming in America", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T15:24:33+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"A graphic that contains an image of a rampaging Typhlosion Pok\u00e9mon in a city in the Pok\u00e9mon anime.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/polygon-mosaic-7.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Typhlosion, the fire-type Pok\u00e9mon, never did anything wrong \u2014 but that hasn\u2019t stopped it from becoming one of the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/465710/pokemon-game-freak-leak-hack\">biggest victims of a recent hack</a>.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Game Freak, the primary studio behind Pok\u00e9mon,\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/analysis/465967/pokemon-game-freak-nintendo-hack-leak\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">suffered a massive data breach</a>. The hacker released thousands of files supposedly pertaining to the creation and development of Pok", "id": 1337366, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon/466096/typhlosion-memes-game-freak-leak", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Pok\u00e9mon Typhlosion has become the pariah of the internet", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T14:16:35+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"The animated animal cast of Sing: Thriller, including gorilla Johnny, pig Gunter, elephant Meena, porcupine Ash, and koala Buster Moon walk together, smiling, through an outdoor space lit with Halloween decorations in Sing: Thriller\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/Thriller.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Illumination\u2019s animated movies <em>Sing</em> and <em>Sing 2</em> are about as harmless, inoffensive, and servicey as they come: They\u2019re <a href=\"https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeyLetsPutOnAShow\">\u201cLet\u2019s put on a show!\u201d</a> movies where animals voiced by celebrities (Matthew McConaughey, Scarlett Johansson, Reese Witherspoon, Nick Kroll, Tori Kelly, Bono, and a whole bunch more) have small problems and anxieties, which they lay to res", "id": 1336994, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/animation-cartoons/466266/sing-halloween-short-netflix-impressions", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Netflix\u2019s new Halloween short Sing: Thriller has one fun idea (which doesn\u2019t matter)", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T13:52:53+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/astro-bot-speedrun-dlc.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">A series of free<strong> speedrun levels DLC</strong> are coming to <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/astro-bot/445530\">Astro Bot</a></em> across Oct. and Nov. 2024.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Each week for five weeks, a new speedrun level will be added to the game, complete with online leaderboards and two additional special bots to find, adding 10 to your overall roster.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">This page explains the <strong>Astro Bot speedrun DLC schedule</strong>, what time each level goes live each day, and the speedrun DLC level requirements.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\" />\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-blo", "id": 1336995, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/astro-bot-guides/466172/speedrun-dlc-levels-update-time-schedule", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "When do Astro Bot\u2019s speedrun DLC levels go live?", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T13:18:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t