figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The second and final season of <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/22800666/arcane-season-1-review\"><em>Arcane</em>, the Netflix animated series based in the world of <em>League of Legends</em></a>, is swiftly approaching. To celebrate the end of Vi, Jinx, and Caitlyn\u2019s story, Riot is releasing <em>Arcane</em> content across its library of games. <em>League of Legends</em>, <em>Teamfight Tactics</em>, <em>Wild Rift</em>, <em>Valorant</em>, and <em>Legends of Runeterra</em> will all be getting new content related to <em>Arcane</em> characters, ranging from a new champion to new cosmetics.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The largest addition is the ", "id": 1336529, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/anime/466236/arcane-content-league-of-legends-valorant", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Riot announces new in-game content across games for the Arcane season 2 launch", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T13:02:51+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/2751125722f24b12702413ce7d1bc1736fa2aa68.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Supergiant Games updated <em>Hades 2</em> on Wednesday with its first major update, called the Olympic Update. <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/24147392/hades-2-early-access-release-date-how-to-play\"><em>Hades 2</em> entered its early access development period</a> in May, and has received several patches since then; Wednesday\u2019s update is the first major content addition, bringing a new region and new weapons, boons, characters, and voice lines.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/news/app/1145350?emclan=103582791472836561&amp;emgid=7057794870234137716\">In an update published to Steam</a>, Supergiant Ga", "id": 1336530, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/466265/hades-2-olympic-update-new-regions-characters-weapons", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Hades 2\u2019s big update adds new region, weapons, and characters", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T12:47:10+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/pokemon.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/pokemon\">Pok\u00e9mon</a> has set X on fire.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">It\u2019s not as if this hasn\u2019t happened before. Fandoms are passionate and even the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23150011/pokemon-violet-scarlet-smoliv-memes-fan-art-gen-9\">reveal of a single cute character</a> can seemingly take over the feeds of thousands of people. But it\u2019s a lot more serious this time.\u00a0</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Over the weekend, Game Freak suffered what could easily be described as the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/news/465710/pokemon-game-freak-leak-hack\">biggest data breach in Pok\u00e9mon history</a>. Everyone and their mother c", "id": 1336531, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pokemon/466078/are-pokemon-leaks-real-game-freak", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to consume Pok\u00e9mon leaks responsibly", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-16T12:32:39+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/ss_2be4cb7277b45b098ffdb965c6eb53329a1f40f8.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">What if we just quit our jobs, moved back home, and started up a frog refuge with our childhood pals? That\u2019s the premise of developer Humble Reeds\u2019 creature collecting game <em>Kamaeru: A Frog Refuge</em>. And it\u2019s a delight. <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2016/1/22/10800378/neko-atsume-review-life-changing\">If you\u2019ve played <em>Neko Atsume</em></a>, you\u2019ll understand the base gameplay of <em>Kamaeru</em> \u2014 attract frogs to your wetlands frog sanctuary. You\u2019ll place furniture and toys on the refuge grounds, build builds and plant reeds, attract bugs to feed the frogs, all to lure them into staying. <em>Kamaeru</em> doesn\u2019t have the same", "id": 1336532, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/gaming/466240/kamaeru-frog-refuge-neko-astume-impressions", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "